## [](#why-not-use-openai-embedding-api)Why Not use openai embedding API

Memfree initially used the openai embedding API, which is very easy to use, and the latest text-embedding-3-large model also supports custom dimensions. The only problem is latency. Even for very short inputs, the openai API latency takes 100 to 200 milliseconds.

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
When you only need to build vector indexes and search services, a latency of more than 100 milliseconds is acceptable. However, when you need a rerank service, a latency of several hundred milliseconds is unacceptable, because the Internet search engine before rerank takes 500 to 1000 milliseconds.

The process of Hybrid AI search is as follows:

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
1.  **Search**: Get answers to user questions from Internet search engines and vectorized databases in parallel
2.  **Rerank**: Sort all relevant contexts according to user similarity and provide the most similar top contexts to LLM
3.  **Answer**: LLM gives the most accurate answer possible based on the context of the search

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text: We hope that the latency of rerank is within tens of milliseconds, so the latency of a single embedding needs to be around a few milliseconds, because the input of rerank is more than 10 vectors.

text: ## [](#how-to-build-fast-local-embedding-service)How to build fast local embedding service

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
### [](#1-first-try-fastembed-js)1 First Try fastembed-js

I have tested the rust version of the fastembed library before, and I know that I can achieve a few milliseconds of latency. But my entire project is currently built on TS. So I first tried the js version of fastembed [https://github.com/Anush008/fastembed-js](https://github.com/Anush008/fastembed-js)

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text: The results are in line with my theoretical expectations. Fastembed-js takes more than 40 milliseconds to embed once.

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
### [](#2-try-fastembed-rs-wasm)2\. Try fastembed-rs WASM

So I can only choose the rust version of fastembed: [https://github.com/Anush008/fastembed-rs](https://github.com/Anush008/fastembed-rs). There are two ways to integrate the rust version of the code with my TS project: WASM and local HTTP service

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text: But when I compiled fastembed-rs into WASM version, I encountered many compilation errors, so I temporarily gave up the WASM method.

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
### [](#3-fastembed-rs-local-http-service)3\. fastembed-rs local HTTP service

Finally, I built a simple embedding service based on fastembed-rs and axum. **The core code is only a few dozen lines, and a single embedding takes only a few milliseconds.**

**The complete code is now open source**: [https://github.com/memfreeme/memfree](https://github.com/memfreeme/memfree)

title: Hybrid AI Search 1 - how to build fast embedding service
text:
### [](#4-how-to-choose-embedding-model)4\. How to choose embedding model

The key points of choosing an embedding model: accuracy, model memory usage and calculation speed, dimension size, and multi-language support.

After testing and trade off these points, I finally chose the sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 model supported by fastembed.
